    <h2 class="font-size-28 mb-font-size-24 margin-bottom-20">
        Key Factors Affecting Electric Bike Range
    </h2>

    <h3 class="font-size-24 mb-font-size-16 margin-bottom-20 margin-top-48">Battery Capacity</h3>
    <p class="margin-bottom-20">
      <span>
        This is a key factor for range. In general, a higher-capacity battery allows for longer rides. A 500Wh battery generally lasts longer than a 250Wh one.
      </span>
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-size-24 mb-font-size-16 margin-bottom-20 margin-top-48">Motor Efficiency</h3>
    <p class="margin-bottom-20">
      <span>
        The motor power has a direct impact on how far you can ride. A higher-wattage motor can provide power for long-distance rides. However, more power can use up the battery quickly if the motor is not efficient.
      </span>
      <br>
      <span>
        Modern electric bikes are equipped with improved motors. These motors provide enough power for tough rides while conserving battery life. This balance allows you to ride longer distances without frequently recharging.
      </span>
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-size-24 mb-font-size-16 margin-bottom-20 margin-top-48">Bike Weight and Design</h3>
    <p class="margin-bottom-20">
      <span>
        Lighter bikes use less energy and travel farther. Aerodynamic designs help reduce drag. Bikes made from materials like aluminum or carbon fiber are preferred for long-distance rides because they are strong and light.
      </span>
    </p>
